## Converter Bug: Missing interface grouping and model collapsing

This issue covers three improvements to the `tsp-openapi3` converter:

1. **Collapse duplicate error response models** (item 1, checked) ‚Äî The converter now uses a `GeneratedHelpers.DefaultResponse` template instead of creating individual response models per operation. This item appears partially addressed.

2. **Group operations with same tag under single interface** (item 2, still open) ‚Äî When converting an OpenAPI3 spec where all operations share the `Widgets` tag, the converter outputs standalone `op` declarations instead of grouping them into an `interface Widgets { ... }`. The current output produces:
   ```typespec
   @tag("Widgets") @route("/widgets") @get op Widgets_list(): ...;
   @tag("Widgets") @route("/widgets") @post op Widgets_create(...): ...;
   ```
   Expected output would be:
   ```typespec
   @tag("Widgets") @route("/widgets") interface Widgets {
     @get op list(): ...;
     @post op create(...): ...;
   }
